  "prompt": "The income paid/credited showing on my 26AS statement is Rs. 1,25,367.44 (salary income) and on Form 16, the total income shown is Rs 1,33,209 (after deducting PF). Which one should I show in ITR 1 under 'Income from Chargeable Salaries'?",
  "response": "You should report the income shown on your **Form 16** in ITR-1 under 'Income from Chargeable Salaries'.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Form 16 is the official document for salary income:** Form 16 is a certificate issued by your employer, detailing the salary paid to you and the tax deducted at source (TDS) on that income. It's the primary document you should use for filing your Income Tax Return (ITR).\n\n*   **26AS is a summary, Form 16 is detailed:** Form 26AS is a consolidated tax statement that shows all the tax credits available to you, including TDS, TCS, and advance tax paid. It's a helpful reference, but it's not always 100% accurate or complete. Discrepancies can occur due to various reasons, such as reporting delays or errors by the deductor.\n\n*   **PF Deduction and Taxable Income:**  The difference between your 26AS (Rs. 1,25,367.44) and Form 16 (Rs 1,33,209) figures is likely due to the inclusion of your PF (Provident Fund) contribution in your gross salary. While your PF contributions are deducted from your taxable income under Section 80C, your gross salary *before* these deductions should be reported as 'Income from Salaries'.\n\nTherefore, use the amount from your Form 16 (Rs 1,33,209) when filing your ITR-1.\n\n**Important:**\n\n*   **Verify Discrepancies:** If you're still concerned about the difference between the amounts, double-check your Form 16 and pay slips for the relevant financial year. Make sure you understand how your PF contributions and other deductions were handled.\n\n*   **Reconcile if Necessary:** If you find an actual error in Form 16, immediately contact your employer's HR/accounts department to get it corrected and reissued.  Then use the corrected Form 16 to file your ITR.\n\nIn summary, use the amount on your Form 16, which is Rs. 1,33,209, under 'Income from Chargeable Salaries' in your ITR-1.\n",
